{
  "stem": "8784.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In English that means, Mr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Schindler, no carpenter was left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "At that time, I had absolutely no idea whether what I was saying was true or not true, because I did not know who was selected and who was standing on one group and who was in the other one.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I only-- I said that because that's the only thing that came to my mind, and I just didn't know what else to say to somehow remain with Oskar Schindler.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I already knew at that time-- I sensed that already-- that remaining with Schindler whatever will be much better than going anyplace else.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Lo and behold, this worked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Oskar Schindler grabbed me by my arm and put me into a group of people that eventually wound up to be a group of 300 people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And these 300 people remained in the concentration camp of Oskar Schindler's, while the other people were delivered in the summer-- end of the summer of 1944, to Krakow-Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The fate of the other people became known to me after the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "At the time of the war, I did not know that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But after the war, it became known to me as a fact that most of those 700 people that were returned to Krakow-Plaszow wound up in other concentration camps, like Mauthausen, like Dachau, like Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, one of my close buddies at that time that I was friendly with in the concentration camp of Oskar Schindler-- since I had no family, I had to glue on to somebody.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So one of those people that I glued onto, became very close with like if we were brothers, was a fellow by the name of Adam Mandel.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
